Truly one of the best coffee-shops in Chicago, and a great place to visit during COVID-19! While in grad school, I often came here to do work at the outdoor patio and drink a lot of their good coffee (weather permitting, of course). However, after moving away, I didn't have the chance to come back to visit until last week, which was delightful. The staff has made such an excellent go of fixing up their space to be accommodating for coffee-lovers and visitors alike, fixing their patio to stagger tables farther apart, ask for guests to wear masks at all times aside from eating/drinking, and closing off an area to have easy access for pickup. I would encourage them to make an effort to limit the number of people allowed on their patio at once (it was a little too busy while I visited), but otherwise encourage people to come visit. Grab a coffee or a scone, and buy some of their delicious avocado toast for a light lunch or snack. Bring your laptop/book if you'd like to work here, but be cautious about COVID-19 restrictions!

I really enjoyed my time here. Even on a busy Saturday, they have lots of space, and the staff was efficient and friendly. This is helped by their “no WiFi Saturdays” from 11am-3pm, as it’s their busiest time of the week, so it helps people flow in and out and makes seats readily available.  I appreciate that there are a lot of options for drink sizes and the prices genuinely seem to reflect the difference in sizes, so you feel like buying the size you want instead of being pressured to get a size smaller because it’s so much cheaper or larger because it’s “just a few cents more.”  I guess my one complaint is the quality of the drink. I liked that their standard is 2% milk rather than whole because that’s a bit healthier and tends to make the flavor of the drink stronger. But for the price, the mocha I got tasted not much like espresso at all. It was very chocolatey, and it tasted like syrupy chocolate and not real chocolate. Don’t get me wrong- I know coffee shops use chocolate syrup. But this tasted like an artificial chocolate rather than a higher quality brand that has a better flavor.  I’m still giving it 4 stars because the vibe and staff are so good. My boyfriend got a plain iced coffee and really liked the coffee flavor, which is high praise from him. Overall I’d come back but probably try a chai or smoothie rather than a flavored latte.
